			<tr>
				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Got owned by Maligar.<a name="14807"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Jan 8 04 6:31 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>Last night I ran around got the invoice, turned in for the doll, turned into the note to daddy and then went to give the note to Maligar.  Killed his punk-a$ buddys and healed back up to full.  Charmed him, and the doppleganger spawned.
<br />

<br />
Quick digression:  I am only level 50 and was too lazy to go get a virtue or any other buffs before I decided to solo this guy.  So clearly I'm not bright.
<br />

<br />
Anyway, when he spawned I had the MR psalm up (which I now know is a mistake) and tried to fear kite the dude.
<br />

<br />
For the most part, fear was sticking and chains was resisted only a few times.  In the three or four times fear did break, however, I learned how Ving Rhames felt in Pulp Fiction.  He got both his poison and disease dots on me multiple times, rooted me and nuked me.  I had him down to 25% before he got both dots on me and I could not heal myself fast enough and died, just like his helpless little stepdaughter.
<br />

<br />
Oh well, I will get that sick fatricidal pederast tonight.  Here is the new plan.  Get virtue and shammy buffs.  Play purifying rythems until fear and snare lands.  Fear kite with chains and Jonathons.  
<br />

<br />
I don't want to get a bunch of guildies to help because I know I can solo this guy.  Any tips in that regard would be appreciated.</span></td>
