				<td colspan="2"><span>I tried Maligar twice not long ago.  First try was on a 55 bard that was donated to my guild by someone who quit the game.  I wanted to see how hard he was before taking my bard out there.  Tried just chanting him down with three chants, died to his dots because I didn't have any resist songs or buffs up.
<br />

<br />
Second try was on my bard(lvl 49 at the time), sang the poison/disease/mr song and two chants and killed him easily.  Didn't have any other buffs except sow.
<br />

<br />
My suggestion, get resist buffs from someone that will last a while, hp buffs, sow, twist in your resist song, how you do the damage after that is up to you, fear kiting or chant kiting, what have you.
<br />
</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
