				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Got owned by Maligar.<a name="14849"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Jan 9 04 8:41 AM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>since almost all of his dots have disease or poison counters involved with them an even faster way to get rid of them is to use our nice little lvl 45 cure song, that way you dont end up dispelling your virtue or fos if you were smart enough to get one.
<br />

<br />
I soloed this guy chant kiting without buffs at lvl 51.
<br />

<br />
Since our chants have such a long range we can use SAC to run in and out of casting range to keep him from landing anything on us.
<br />

<br />
I used the lev from my SS boots and SAC to do just that, then ran into target range every few seconds to make sure my chants hit him.
<br />

<br />
He did take me down to about 50% but this is a trick I learned long ago when dealing with casters in a place where you have so much room to run.
<br />

<br />
Most times you can run out of range between the time they start casting and the time it would land<img src="/skins/default/images/emotions/emotion-1.gif" border="0" alt="Smiley" hspace="2" /></span></td>
			</tr><tr>
