				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Got owned by Maligar.<a name="16925"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Jan 23 04 7:40 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>Last night I decided to start work on my epic and I got up to this point, you can kinda do the torch run and Maligar quest at the same time. At the time I was level 57 unbuffed with only Dark Elf Illusion and SAC song buff. Even with the Dark Elf illusion I still con'd Scowls. I took with me a friend, 58 Wiz, and I pulled all of Maligar's friends one at a time (they were all green, and Maligar was LightBlue) Each of the greenies was easy. I would pull them down the hill and engage while I twisted the 3 chant songs.
<br />
When it came to Maligar I ran up to him and he attacked me before I could hand in the note, so I charmed him and handed in the note and immediately the charm broke because he was now the doppelganger. I fought him the same way I fought his cronies and never got below 75% health. I resisted all of his spells with the exception of his DD spells, (my health is 17-1800). My Wiz friend blasted him once maybe twice total. Grabbed his head and carreid it around for a while before turning it in, just to have some fun. 
<br />
So there you are....tales from a 57 unbuffed bard.<img src="/skins/default/images/emotions/emotion-1.gif" border="0" alt="Smiley" hspace="2" /> </span></td>
