				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Got owned by Maligar.<a name="19807"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Feb 8 04 3:57 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>Not to dredge up a slightly old thread, but I dispatched Maligar today with ease and thought I'd share my approach.
<br />

<br />
I'm a level 53 bard and only have 1750 hps. Although I was perhaps foolish, I did not get any buffs for this attempt.
<br />

<br />
All I did was to approach Maligar and see that he was threatening to me. So, as mentioned in other posts, I clicked the DE mask. Now he was scowling. Doh! Oh well, that is neither here nor there. I charmed him and, instead of coming solo, his entire entourage was behind him--I thought they were after me, being scowling, but now that he was my pet, they were after him naturally. How convenient. I had him attack and kill the entourage. Adds dispatched. 
<br />

<br />
Once they were dead I simply sang Purifying Rythms and turned my note into him. The doppleganger popped and I easily chant-kited him with two chants plus the resist song. He died easily and did not land a single spell on me. I wasn't even HT'd.
<br />

<br />
Anyway, I thought I'd share if only to re-affirm to apprehensive bards around my level that he is quite doable.<img src="/skins/default/images/emotions/emotion-1.gif" border="0" alt="Smiley" hspace="2" />
<br />

<br />
-Teryz 
<br />
Povar</span></td>
